headline: Super Micro Computer Stock Sinks Again on Guidance. Is It Time to Buy the Dip?
summary: Supermicro shares fell once again after the company issued weak guidance.  It has struggled with margin pressure and forecasting revenue.  After seeing its shares tumble when the company pre-announced disappointing fiscal third-quarter results, Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ: SMCI) stock was once again falling after the company reported its full results and issued weak guidance.
